acceptBid(uint256,uint256).details: when the user who created a sell-order for the nft wants to accept a bid he must call this function

params._bidId: the id's of bid that the sell-order's creator accepted
params._orderId: the id's of the sell-order note the bid or order must not be ended or canceled before calling this function

createBid(uint256,address,uint256).details: user can create a bid for a arbitrary nft by calling this function

params._orderId: the order-id that user wants to make a bid for that
params._price: the price of the bid user wishes to make for the order note before creating bid user must approve marketplace contract to access his/her tokens
params._token: the currency that user wants to pay with

createERC721Contract(string,string,strin.details: each wallet can create a full-owned NFT contract for them selves by calling this function

createSellOrder(address,uint256,address,.details: user can create a sell-order on the market by calling this function

params._contractAddr: the contract address that user has some nft and wants to create sell-order for that
params._nftId: the nft that user wants to sell
params._price: the price of this sell-order note before creating sell-order user must approve marketplace contract to access his/her nft
params._token: the currency that user wants to use (it must be a valid token in marketplace)
